FBIS4-48482 "drafr098_e_94015" FBIS-AFR-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Official on Preparations for 23 May Ward Elections Official on Preparations for 23 May Ward Elections AB1905215094 Lagos NTA Television Network in English 2000 GMT 19 May 94 AB1905215094 Lagos NTA Television Network English BFN [Text] Over 100,000 polling stations have been designated voting centers throughout the country, for the election next Monday [23 May] of ward delegates to the Constitutional Conference. The chairman of the National Constitutional Conference Election Committee, Mr. Bernard Mba, gave this figure in Abuja in an interview with correspondent Yusuf Adi on the general preparations for the ward delegates election: [Begin recording] [Adi] The Conference Election Committee chairman, Mr. Bernard Mba, also disclosed that each polling center (?will be manned) by three officials to guide voters through the election process. He emphasized that the open ballot system [words indistinct] voters. Mr. Mba said the commission has completed the dispatch of all the necessary materials to all the states for the successful conduct of the exercise. Also, to ease transportation problems, Mr. Mba said fuel has been provided to the (?committee's offices) in the states for movement of persons and materials. He then called for the necessary cooperation to make the exercise worthwhile. [Mba] Monday, 23 May, has been declared a public holiday, to make it easy for Nigerians to go out to the polling stations nearest to their homes, and vote and select the candidates of their choice. This is a very crucial, very important election, an election which marks the first step towards a return to democracy. [passage indistinct] [end recording]
